Samuel MarksonWednesday, August 7, 2013 at 6:25am UTC+04

Hmm, I would recommend Trader Joe's. There is one on Boylston street that is a good walk if the weather is nice. It is near the Hynes Convention center T stop (on the green line--but you should walk). In Central Square there is the Harvest Co-op grocery, along with a good Indian and Korean market. There is food open late in central square (pizza, falafel, etc.) Around MIT, there is a convenience store in the student center. But if you are hungry now, I recommend walking to central square (up Massachusetts Avenue). Near Fenway, there is a Shaw's that is open 24 hours a day, but it is fairly far away, so I can't recommend it now. I myself am not sure where to order a meal--many pizza places (Domino's, for example) will do this. So if you don't feel like moving, they will deliver it to you. Good luck. Are you in Cambridge until the end of August?

Ehsan Ul HaqThursday, November 7, 2013 at 11:36pm UTC+04

Programmers have a surprisingly intimate relationship with the programming languages they use. Your programming language will frustrate you, and enlighten you. Over time you will learn your programming language's inner workings and little quirks. It will get inside your head, too, and change the way your mind works. Choose the right programming language and together you will create something new and beautiful. Choose wrongly and things can get very messy indeed. In other words, choosing a programming language is much like choosing a romantic partner... (Note: I'm a straight guy. If you're not, feel free to do a mental find/replace with whatever you're into). PHP is your teenage sweetheart, the girl you first awkwardly fumbled around with that one summer. Just don't try and start a more serious relationship - this girl has serious issues. Perl is PHP's older sister. She might be a bit old for you, but she was pretty popular back in the 90s. In a long-term relationship with Larry Wall, so her standards have dropped, and she's looking seriously fugly now. "I don't care what y'all say, I still love her!", he says. No-one else does. Ruby is the cool kid of the scripting family. When you first saw her, she took your breath away with her beauty. She was fun, too. At the time she seemed a bit slow and ditzy - though she's matured a lot in the last few years. Python is Ruby's more sensible sister. She's elegant, classy, and sophisticated. She's perhaps too perfect. Most guys are like "dude, how can you not like Python!?". Sure, you like Python. You just consider her the boring version of the edgy and romantic Ruby. Java is a successful career woman. Some people who've worked with her feel she owes her position less to ability and more to her knack for impressing the middle-management types. You might feel that she's the sensible type you should settle down with. Just prepare for years of "NO THAT DOESNT GO THERE GOD YOU ALWAYS USE THE WRONG TYPE INTERFACE AND YOU MISSED A SEMICOLON" nagging. C++ is Java's cousin. Similar to Java in many ways, the main difference being she grew up in a more innocent time and doesn't believe in using protection. By "protection", I mean automatic memory management, of course. What did you think I meant? C is C++'s mom. Mention her name to some old grey beard hackers and they're sure to reminisce with a twinkle in their eye. Objective C is another member of the C family. She joined that weird church a while back, and won't date anyone outside of it. Haskell, Clojure, Scheme and their friends are those hipster, artsy, intellectual girls you probably spent a blissful college summer with a few years ago. The first girls who really challenged you. Of course, it could never have become something more serious (you tell yourself). Though you'll always be left asking "what if?" You might be put off C# due to her family's reputation. But they've gone legit, the last few years, they tell you. Once you're one of us, you're one of us, you hear? You need a database? Her brother MSSQL will hook you up. Need a place to stay? Heck, her daddy will even buy you your own mansion on Azure avenue. What's that, you're having second thoughts about all these overly friendly relatives? No, you can never leave. You're part of the family, now, ya hear? Javascript - hey, wasn't that the girl you first kissed, way before even PHP came on the scene? I wonder what she's doing now. I hear her career's really taken off in the last few years. Would be cool to catch up some time, if only for old time's sake... (You catch sight of her, dressed head to toe in designer jQuery)... wow, somebody grew into a beautiful swan...

Tim BalbekovFriday, October 11, 2013 at 1:45pm UTC+04

assume you are referring to the Halbach magnet I built for my PhD thesis. This magnet uses a non-linear gradient field for image encoding which means that the image resolution is non-uniform. We are achieving close to 1mm resolution near the periphery but it degrades to 2cm blur in the center of the image (we have ideas for fixing this problem though).

Roman PrilepskiyThursday, October 10, 2013 at 9:48am UTC+04

Hey, guys! Some info from my medical friend. 1) We really should be aware of how much radiation our device could produce (I mean Tesla). Low one -> We won't see scanned results perfectly. 2) Radiation influence is not so clear. It's not recommended to pregnant women to take part in MRI, people with cardiostimulators and metal in bodies are also forbidden to use it. 3) Frequent radiation is bad for health, so we should think about how we are going to protect doctors in case of using it in ambulances. 4) MRI is definitely better than X-ray. Cause you have perfect results from each scanned layer. 5) MRI is mostly used for scanning joints and the head. 6) In case of using it for sportsmen, portable MRI makes sense during championships or Olympic games.

Sergey IvanovThursday, September 26, 2013 at 2:11pm UTC+04

Muscle volume was also quantified in Iberian ham. 10 The use of MRI with a fully automated image analysis method for the recognition of biceps femoris and semi-membranous muscles allowed a study of the evolution of their volume during ripening. The correlation between image analysis and dissection yielded R 2 values up to 0.94. The sequence used involved a T 1 -weighted spin echo and samples were scanned at room temperature. The contrast between fat and muscle increased during ripening due to the drying of muscle over time. The loss of weight was related to the decreasing size of the muscles measured by MRI, with a R 2 of 0.99. Studies have also been performed on pig carcasses. For these studies, images were acquired at 4 ◦ C, when the fat was partially crystallized and gave a low signal. The maximum contrast between fat and muscle was achieved using a gradient-echo sequence. Moreover, an MRI method allowing quantification of both subcutaneous fat and intermuscular fat has been proposed. The image analysis quantified the fat and the muscle, with the refinement of taking partial volume, i.e., voxels containing both fat and muscle, into account (Figure 2). 11 The MRI results were compared with dissection, giving a R 2 of 0.95 to 0.98 for fat and 0.92 to 0.99 for subcutaneous fat depending on the cut.

Rustam AkhtyamovThursday, September 26, 2013 at 2:06pm UTC+04

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FYTLWmgqyMc

Sergey IvanovThursday, September 26, 2013 at 2:06pm UTC+04

MRI has been used to quantify body composition in animals both in vivo and postmortem (pigs, sheep, and poultry). In both cases, the high contrast between fat and muscle in images was used to separate such tissues, either manually or with the help of an automatic image segmentation algorithm. The sequences used were mainly dependent on the characteristics of the fat (saturated or nonsaturated) linked to the species studied and the temperature measurement. For example, lean and fat tissues were quantified in living pigs and sheep using a four-echo spin-echo sequence. 8 Tissue segmentation was performed using a classification algorithm based on four levels of intensity. The results were compared with those found by dissection of the animals, and high correlation coefficient R 2 values (between 0.89 and 0.97) were obtained for different weight groups. Estimation of poultry breast meat yield was assessed by MRI. 9 Images were acquired just after killing, providing a similar contrast with living animals. The volume of breast muscle was computed using a mixture of automatic and manual segmentation and the relationship between MRI and dissection led to a R 2 of 0.96 for breast meat volume and 0.92 for breast meat yield.

заболевания конечностей, как правило, сопровождающиеся патологической болью, вызывают падение уровня естественной агрессивности животных и ведут к дезадаптации, утрате способности конкурировать за место у кормушки и. как следствие, снижается потребление сухого вещества. Это приводит к уменьшению запасов питательных веществ в организме, потере веса, снижению продуктивности, нарушению оплодотворяемости и. в конце концов, к выбраковке.

First of all - about road quality checking with MRI: - http://web.anl.gov/PCS/acsfuel/preprint%20archive/Files/41_4_ORLANDO_08-96_1327.pdf (In this study, exploratory MRI measurements were made on the precipitation of asphaltenes from asphalt, observation of natural rubber in asphalt, and the possible interaction of water with asphalt at an aggregate interface. The MRI experiments showed that image contrast between asphaltenes and the precipitating solvent can be improved by varying the echo time used to form the images. Natural rubber in the presence of asphalt can be observed using 3D imaging methods, leading to the possibility of studying solvent swelling and possible dissolution of crumb rubber by components of the asphalt. MRI measurements of asphaltlwatedaggregate systems showed evidence of water penetration at the aggregate interface.) - 1) The Frontiers of Nonmedical MRI - a book http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00723-007-0015-2 Maybe you know some sites where we can download it. 2) Journal of Magnetic Resonance, FREE http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/10907807/235 3) !!! Magnetic Resonance of Porous Media (MRPM): A perspective http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1090780712003473 4) MRI of plants and foods http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1090780713000037 + cool video of MRI imaging of fruits http://digimri.com/en/nauka-and-tehnica/nemedicinskie-primenenia-mri/292-ovoshi-frukty-mrt 5) Magnetic resonance velocimetry: applications of magnetic resonance imaging in the measurement of fluid motion http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs00348-007-0383-2 6) Magnetic Resonance Imaging - Application Tips from Siemens http://www.healthcare.siemens.com/magnetic-resonance-imaging/magnetom-world/clinical-corner/application-tips 7) !!! Another application for MRI which is inspired by muscle structure is thoroughbred health evaluation. The level of medical treatment given to thoroughbreds is far superior than for horses of lesser financial value. And yet a broken leg is often death-threatening because weight should be equally distributed. MRI is used to qualify muscles. Market: thoroughbred holders; circus;

Sergey IvanovTuesday, September 24, 2013 at 5:44am UTC+04

Sergey IvanovTuesday, September 24, 2013 at 5:43am UTC+04

Use of MRI to understand microstructure of food and to measure heat transfer is regularly increasing. Implementation of MRI systems dedicated to food systems is required. Demand of MRI systems that are more oriented in food applications proposed new solutions: smaller magnet size, the magnetic field is lower because of the susceptibility artifacts induced by air bubbles, and the magnetic pulsed field gradient strengths are stronger. Applications: 1. Fruits and Vegetables. MRI is used to investigate internal structure and physical state of water in fruits and vegetable tissues. It can provide both indirect and direct information at both cell and macroscopic levels. This information is used during development, ripening, and storage, and to evaluate various internal quality factors such as browning. Market: Academia; genetic engineers; agriculture 2. Fat and Muscle Quantification. MRI is used to quantify body composition in animals. Contrast between fat and muscles is used to separate tissues. Market: Farms 3. Muscle Structure MRI is used to qualify muscles by determining fat distribution and muscle water. With an appropriate choice of MR pulse detectors, 3-D distribution of fat, water, collagen, and salt in th muscles can be accessed. Collagen content is one of the major meat quality parameters that determine overall acceptability by the consumer. Market: Meat plants, McDonald's. 4. Dairy Products and Processes Dairy proteins can be destabilized and denatured in different ways leading to the formation of gel with different structures. Different types of information can be extracted such as location of whey, the amount of whey and others. The potential of MRI has been evaluated for the investigation of cheese ripening. The number of holes was determined and the thinness ratio, cross-sectional area, and hole-center locations were calculated. Also used for the classification of soft cheese. Market: Dairy products industry; devices for cheese-making for cooks 5. Temperature Measurements Classical methods for verification of heat transfer are limited as temperature is measured at only a few discrete points. To overcome temperature maps are built. Temperature maps are important for identifying hot and cold regions in processing operations such as sterilization and pasteurization and for measurement of temperature distribution induced by heating of food. MRI is the only technique for temperature mapping in food that allows noninvasive 2- and 3-D measurement of heating patterns, making it possible to characterize products both locally and dynamically. Special MRI device was built in microwave oven to make heating experiments with real food. MRI temperature mapping has been used to compare the heating patterns induced by different frying methods, including deep fat frying and use of a microwave oven, and to evaluate the effects of frying time. Market: Oven companies; thermostats companies;

Tim BalbekovMonday, September 23, 2013 at 2:07pm UTC+04

"Indirect or closed loop systems use a heat exchanger that separates the potable water from the fluid, known as the "heat-transfer fluid" (HTF), that circulates through the collector. The two most common HTFs are water and an antifreeze/water mix that typically uses non-toxic propylene glycol. After being heated in the panels, the HTF travels to the heat exchanger, where its heat is transferred to the potable water. Though slightly more expensive, indirect systems offer freeze protection and typically offer overheat protection as well."

Tim BalbekovMonday, September 23, 2013 at 2:07pm UTC+04

Winter efficiency analysis: We have two options, either we push water into the solar panel, and shut it off in the winter to prevent it from freezing. Or, we use a heat exchanger with antifreeze liquid, which lets us run it in the winter, but we lose efficiency during the heat exchange process in the summer. Either way, our goal here is to get that 1.5kWh/m2/day during the 3 winter months without losing that amount in the summer, while keeping costs down. 1. Perform water winter efficiency analysis (including cost, energy savings) 2. Perform heat exchanger winter efficiency analysis 3. Draw a diagram of the resulting system 4. Draw the stupid "red sea" diagram shit 5. Write up a bill of materials to justify the cost Pick one

В общем согласно документации heroku для того чтобы привязать корневой домен karfidovlab.ru (root domain) к herokuapp нужно либо использовать особые типы dns records (только у некоторых dns провайдеров есть, у нашего нет), либо использовать перенаправление (web-forwarding) сайта на www.karfidovlab.ru. Для нас работает только второй вариант, но он не включен в стоимость основных услуг на mnogodomenov, стоит 120 руб/год. Я сейчас оплатил, перенаправил, но пока изменения не вступили в силу. Говорят может до 48 часов проходить пока не вступит. Придется подождать. www.karfidovlab.ru работает, и большинство браузеров переводит добавляет в начало адреса. Ссылки про привязку: https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/apex-domains, https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/custom-domains, http://www.one.com/en/support/guide/manage-your-dns-settings

В рамках проекта я выполняю следующие задачи: — руковожу командой iOS-разработчиков, из трёх человек + я: составления плана на двухнедельные спринты, распределение задач, налаживание взаимодействия между членами командами, ответственность за выполнение поставленных целей в срок, помощь в случае каких-либо недопониманий. — сам являюсь iOS разработчиком, занимаюсь работой с данными и взаимодействие с сервером (что, по сути, тоже работа с данными). В эти два месяца планируется внедрение новых языковых пар и выход на новые международные рынки, что потребует существенных переработок в структуре данных и процесса обучения. — буду внедрять новые, адаптирующиеся алгоритмы выдачи слов пользователям. Совместно с Виктором Сафроновым, специалистом по ML, который также работает в нашей команде и является ментором пары проектов в Сколтехе, мы будем изменять то, как выдаются слова пользователю, подстраиваться по тематиками и сложностям, анализировать их влияние на время пребывания человека в приложении. Тут может быть немного инновационности как таковой) — так как мы будем выходить на новые рынки в это время, могу участвовать в анализе различных поведенческих воронок и изменении приложения, в соответствии с ними, с целю повышения ключевых показателей.

Dear Alexander: On behalf of the MSc Admissions Committee at the Skolkovo Institute of Science and Technology, it is my pleasure to inform you of your selection as a finalist for the Skoltech MSc Program in Information Science and Technology, starting from approximately August 1, 2014. Admission to Skoltech is highly competitive, and we would like to congratulate you on your success! The Skoltech MSc Program begins with a one-month 6-credit course, the Innovation Workshop, which will be offered in Skolkovo for the first time in August 2014. All finalists of the MSc Program are expected to participate in the Workshop, so please plan any summer vacation accordingly. Following the end of the Innovation Workshop, regular Skoltech courses will begin in early September. The academic conditions of this offer are the following: Award of your degree from Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology in summer 2014, prior to enrollment at Skoltech Submission of 3 letters of recommendation and statement of purpose by 14 April Result of 79 or higher on iBT (TOEFL) or 6.5 or higher on IELTS, or above 550 on ITP TOEFL --- you achieved a score of 500/677 on the ITP offered at Skoltech on 14 March 2014. Please note that there may be a possibility for Skoltech to enroll you in an intensive English-langauge course at the New Economic School in the summertime. For all admitted students, Skoltech shall provide an internationally competitive fellowship that includes a tuition waiver, monthly stipend, the possibility to serve as a research, teaching, or innovation assistant, and medical insurance. Housing for students in Skolkovo is not yet constructed (current Skoltech students are renting rooms and apartments in Moscow, often together in groups of two or three). The faculty, staff and the current students at Skoltech look forward to welcoming you into our community in the summer of 2014! To reserve your place in the program, please respond to this email no later than 09:00 (Moscow time) on Monday, 14 April 2014 (you are more than welcome to respond earlier, of course!). Following receipt of your confirmation, Skoltech will begin the process of arranging the documents necessary for your matriculation to Skoltech.

Sergey Ivanov, George Milyutin
Sergey IvanovSunday, October 12, 2014 at 11:24pm UTC+04

Вот каноническая статья, с которой все началось. 2003 года. http://www.cs.cornell.edu/home/kleinber/kdd03-inf.pdf

Sergey IvanovSunday, October 12, 2014 at 11:22pm UTC+04

В любом случае, я немного другим занимаюсь в своей научной работе. Математики занимаются описанием моделей графов и их характеристиками типа clustering coefficients. Это статические вещи. В cs иет скорее поиск динамических вещей типа распространения информации от разных моделей их распространения. Там вопрос того является ли этот граф random или scale-free опускается (наверно зря, но проблем и так хватает). В краю угла ставится вопрос о том как можно максимизировать распространение информации (ну или поведения). Мой доклад был скорее о том какие факторы могут повлиять на эту информации (какие-то статические типа degree или динамические история влияния в прошлом).
